         <notesStmt>
            <note>
								David Finzi ben Menahem Finzi (or Panzi?): inscribed with his name (folio 424r 424r). 
								Eliyaḳim ben Hosheʿa Finzi (or Panzi?): sold it to Yaʿaḳov ben Avraham of Sforno on Tuesday 29 April 5271  (1511) (folio 11r). Illegible inscription in Latin characters (folio 374r). 
								Jacob Geraldino, censor: inscribed with his name, 12 December 1555  (folio 422v); see 104. 
								Luigi da Bologna, a converted Jew working for the Inquisition as censor (active at the end of the sixteenth, beginning of seventeenth century): inscribed with his name as censor: 'Visto per mi Fra Luigi da Bologna del 1602 in Reggio' (folio 422v); see 104. </note>
            <note type="relatedResource">
								Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.
							</note>
